We will never ask you to log on or provide sensitive information via a link in an email or SMS. If received DELETE IMMEDIATELY. Remember to Stop 🛑, Check 🔎 and Reject ❌ calls, emails and messages that look suspicious.

SCAM ALERT! Beware of a circulating text message scam pretending to be from CommBank. The text requests recipients to click a link to secure their account. These are not legitimate CommBank communications. Do not click the links, call or reply to the sender.
Remember, always Stop 🛑, Check 🔎 and Reject ❌ any calls, emails and messages that look suspicious

2024 Cyber Safety outs:  ❌ Clicking links or opening attachments that look   suspicious ❌ “password123” and all forms of password recycling ❌ Believing you’ve won a draw you didn’t enter ❌ Making payments with gift cards
